<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-03-03</DATELINE><TITLE>Stepping up infection control measures in ophthalmology during the novel coronavirus outbreak: an experience from Hong Kong</TITLE><BODY>Coronavirus disease (COVID-19) has rapidly emerged as a global health threat. The purpose of this article is to share our local experience of stepping up infection control measures in ophthalmology to minimise COVID-19 infection of both healthcare workers and patients.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>